A GROUP of 11 men who were assisted by Somagwaza Institute to go to the mountain for initiation have returned. The organisation helped the group of men who are between the ages of 26 and 47, whose families where unable to assist. With the contributions of community members and other companies, the institute managed to take the men to the mountain and bring them back as men. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments On Friday, 6 January, family members and members of the community took to the streets to welcome the men back home. On Saturday, about 200 people gathered at Khwezi Hall in Gugulethu for umgidi celebrations for the group. The families said they do not have enough words to thank the institute and those who have assisted their family members.